tall, not have much fat at all

00:26:48.170 --> 00:26:49.140 align:middle line:90%
on their body.

00:26:49.140 --> 00:26:52.870 align:middle line:84%
And it's a completely
unattainable ideal.

00:26:52.870 --> 00:26:56.040 align:middle line:84%
So yes, I do feel like
we need to be empowered

00:26:56.040 --> 00:27:00.640 align:middle line:84%
around understanding what
it looks like to nurture

00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:03.240 align:middle line:90%
ourselves, to nourish ourselves.

00:27:03.240 --> 00:27:05.460 align:middle line:84%
Now, we all have
different ways to do that.

00:27:05.460 --> 00:27:07.100 align:middle line:84%
For some people,
it's meditation.

00:27:07.100 --> 00:27:09.870 align:middle line:84%
For some people,
it's learning how

00:27:09.870 --> 00:27:12.630 align:middle line:84%
to hit that pause
button, the off button.

00:27:12.630 --> 00:27:16.410 align:middle line:84%
But when it comes to this
standard that we have for

00:27:16.410 --> 00:27:19.560 align:middle line:84%
ourselves-- and you mentioned
my great-grandmother.

00:27:19.560 --> 00:27:22.540 align:middle line:84%
She was not wearing skinny
jeans, you're absolutely right.

00:27:22.540 --> 00:27:24.294 align:middle line:84%
She didn't have
