that they could barely breathe.

00:29:56.825 --> 00:29:59.449 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They didn't know then
you can just have them removed.

00:29:59.449 --> 00:30:02.329 align:middle line:90%


00:30:02.329 --> 00:30:03.120 align:middle line:90%
>>GOTTFRIED: Right.

00:30:03.120 --> 00:30:04.940 align:middle line:90%
Look at how popular Spanx are.

00:30:04.940 --> 00:30:07.300 align:middle line:84%
It's not that we're
so different now.

00:30:07.300 --> 00:30:10.020 align:middle line:84%
And what I think
is important to me

00:30:10.020 --> 00:30:13.180 align:middle line:84%
is a level of
freedom, and a level

00:30:13.180 --> 00:30:16.800 align:middle line:84%
of being able to authentically
pursue your dream,

00:30:16.800 --> 00:30:17.920 align:middle line:90%
whatever that is.

00:30:17.920 --> 00:30:20.570 align:middle line:84%
I think in terms of
Hollywood, of Kate Hepburn.

00:30:20.570 --> 00:30:22.900 align:middle line:90%
I think of Meryl Streep.

00:30:22.900 --> 00:30:26.265 align:middle line:84%
I am riveted every time
I watch Meryl Streep.

00:30:26.265 --> 00:30:27.890 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't matter what
role she's playing.

00:30:27.890 --> 00:30:30.560 align:middle line:84%
She can be Maggie Thatcher
with Alzheimer's disease

00:30:30.560 --> 00:30:32.790 align:middle line:90%
and I am crazy for her.

00:30:32.790 --> 00:30:36.640 align:middle line:84%
I don't mind if she's got 10
or 20 extra pounds on her.

00:30:36.640 --> 00:30:38.670 align:middle line:90%
I think she looks glorious.

00:30:38.670 --> 00:30:40.150 align:middle line:90%
She is radiant.

00:30:40.150 --> 00:30:43.790 align:middle line:84%
So to me, it's
more about agency.

00:30:43.790 --> 00:30:48.700 align:middle line:84%
It's more about freedom
and empowerment.

00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:51.570 align:middle line:84%
Really, women having
more choices, not fewer.

00:30:51.570 --> 00:30:57.210 align:middle line:84%
So if we're trying to weigh
120 pounds maybe 5 foot 5,

00:30:57.210 --> 00:30:59.870 align:middle line:90%
there's a cost to that.

00:30:59.870 --> 00:31:04.470 align:middle line:84%
If you go on Atkins because
you're trying to lose your fat,

00:31:04.470 --> 00:31:06.360 align:middle line:90%
that raises cortisol.

00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:09.420 align:middle line:84%
Turns out that cortisol
not just depletes you

00:31:09.420 --> 00:31:11.900 align:middle line:84%
of your happy brain chemicals
and gives you a muffin top,

00:31:11.900 --> 00:31:15.880 align:middle line:84%
it also accelerates
the aging of your skin.

00:31:15.880 --> 00:31:18.680 align:middle line:84%
So it affects the
skin about 20 x more

00:31:18.680 --> 00:31:19.930 align:middle line:90%
than other parts of your body.

00:31:19.930 --> 00:31:21.820 align:middle line:84%
And this is really
a place where I

00:31:21.820 --> 00:31:26.840 align:middle line:84%
think hormone balance and
health is present outside.

00:31:26.840 --> 00:31:29.290 align:middle line:84%
It's a reflection of
what's happening inside.

00:31:29.290 --> 00:31:32.219 align:middle line:84%
Your skin is a mirror of
what's happening in your mind.

00:31:32.219 --> 00:31:33.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very good point

00:31:33.260 --> 00:31:34.830 align:middle line:84%
>>GOTTFRIED: So I think that's
an important piece as well.

00:31:34.830 --> 00:31:35.491 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:31:35.491 --> 00:31:35.990 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:31:35.990 --> 00:31:39.280 align:middle line:84%
So let's start looking at
some of the simple things.

00:31:39.280 --> 00:31:43.460 align:middle line:84%
We're going to go to more on
a chemical level in the body.

00:31:43.460 --> 00:31:46.760 align:middle line:84%
When we look at some
of the top interrupters

00:31:46.760 --> 00:31:49.560 align:middle line:84%
for balanced hormones,
what are some of the things

00:31:49.560 --> 00:31:50.255 align:middle line:90%
that we take in?

00:31:50.255 --> 00:31:51.390 align:middle line:90%
You say fork.

00:31:51.390 --> 00:31:53.550 align:middle line:84%
The fork to the mouth is
really an important part.

00:31:53.550 --> 00:31:55.920 align:middle line:84%
And look at where the
interrupters are happening

00:31:55.920 --> 00:31:58.170 align:middle line:84%
and then look at how we
can begin restoring them.

00:31:58.170 --> 00:32:00.330 align:middle line:84%
How we can begin restoring
cortisol naturally.

00:32:00.330 --> 00:32:01.680 align:middle line:90%
You talked about this one case.

00:32:01.680 --> 00:32:03.690 align:middle line:84%
But there are other
things we can do too.

00:32:03.690 --> 00:32:05.309 align:middle line:84%
There are herbal
remedies as well.

00:32:05.309 --> 00:32:06.850 align:middle line:84%
And I'd like to get
into some of them

00:32:06.850 --> 00:32:09.610 align:middle line:84%
so people can see
themselves in this story.

00:32:09.610 --> 00:32:10.680 align:middle line:90%
>>GOTTFRIED: Sure, sure.

00:32:10.680 --> 00:32:12.700 align:middle line:84%
And I really think
it's important to say

00:32:12.700 --> 00:32:18.050 align:middle line:84%
that the cool part here is
this isn't some huge project.

00:32:18.050 --> 00:32:19.690 align:middle line:90%
Small hinges swing big doors.

00:32:19.690 --> 00:32:21.630 align:middle line:84%
So I'm really happy
to talk about what's

00:32:21.630 --> 00:32:24.840 align:middle line:84%
proven and also these smaller
things that you can be doing.

00:32:24.840 --> 00:32:28.530 align:middle line:84%
Maybe as you listen today,
maybe what I would want,

00:32:28.530 --> 00:32:31.690 align:middle line:84%
what I would prescribe, is
to pick one or two things

00:32:31.690 --> 00:32:33.640 align:middle line:90%
that we're talking about today.

00:32:33.640 --> 00:32:35.480 align:middle line:84%
So the other piece that
I think is important

00:32:35.480 --> 00:32:39.640 align:middle line:84%
is that when it comes
to hormone imbalance,

00:32:39.640 --> 00:32:42.200 align:middle line:84%
it's easier to
rebalance your hormones

00:32:42.200 --> 00:32:45.650 align:middle line:84%
than to live with the
misery of hormone imbalance.

00:32:45.650 --> 00:32:49.190 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's an important
piece to take away as well.

00:32:49.190 --> 00:32:53.270 align:middle line:84%
So when it comes to what do you
do, what are the interruptors,

00:32:53.270 --> 00:32:57.580 align:middle line:84%
I think about the interrupters
in a systematic way.

00:32:57.580 --> 00:32:59.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you're really
big on scientific studies.

00:32:59.910 --> 00:33:00.700 align:middle line:90%
>>GOTTFRIED: Huge.

00:33:00.700 --> 00:33:02.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So I want to
just say that for you

00:33:02.640 --> 00:33:06.320 align:middle line:84%
that it's not
conjecture on your part.

00:33:06.320 --> 00:33:09.385 align:middle line:84%
You really follow what
works by way of the studies.

00:33:09.385 --> 00:33:11.260 align:middle line:84%
>>GOTTFRIED: Well, this
is an important piece

00:33:11.260 --> 00:33:13.820 align:middle line:84%
that you're raising,
because not only do I

00:33:13.820 --> 00:33:16.300 align:middle line:84%
believe that women
deserve the best

00:33:16.300 --> 00:33:19.330 align:middle line:84%
evidence behind any
recommendation that's made.

00:33:19.330 --> 00:33:21.580 align:middle line:84%
That's true for
men too, but women

00:33:21.580 --> 00:33:24.640 align:middle line:84%
are the ones that were part of
this vast, uncontrolled medical

00:33:24.640 --> 00:33:28.020 align:middle line:84%
experiment for 57 years
in the United States.

00:33:28.020 --> 00:33:32.100 align:middle line:84%
When Premarin was one of the
most popular prescriptions.

00:33:32.100 --> 00:33:32.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:33:32.870 --> 00:33:35.380 align:middle line:84%
>>GOTTFRIED: So it's a form
of estrogen that was used.

00:33:35.380 --> 00:33:37.925 align:middle line:84%
